<br>
The original thread is here:  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showMessage?topicID=399.topic">What are we to do about Command of Druzzil?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
To summarize recent developments and continue:<br>
<br>
There are at least two reports of charmed mobs with over 300 DPS, not including down time, including at least one parsed log.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Goladus</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> claims that the mana required to support this tactic is about 15 mana per tick, including both the enchanter and the priest to support them.  Priest support required is comparable to that required for melee.<br>
<br>
Specific responses:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dumonyu:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Has it occurred to any of the would be nerfers that the game is not just about &quot;Let's make a group and go get XP&quot; to all of us? Even if it was, is CoD hurting your ability to do this? No. You are jealous. Plain and simple.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->If enchanters do 300+ DPS, then there is no room for damage dealers other than enchanters, especially as the game becomes more difficult.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dumonyu:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  like CoD and others are going to be ESSENTIAL for GUILDS to finish PoP as it is designed.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->If true, this makes things even worse.  Enchanters will be required, and every non-charming damage class becomes a relative liability.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dumonyu:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Some of us will actually finish the game, but not if people keep crying to gimp every class that they feel is better than them in some way.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Having twice or perhaps three times the the DPS of non-charming damage dealers, especially melees, is well beyond <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;better in some way.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Indeed, if true, it threatens to make obselete <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">all</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> melee damage dealers.  To the extent that charm is available, applicable, and appropriate, there is no reason to choose a rogue over an enchanter in a group.  Ditto for any other dealer who is unable to charm an appropriate mob.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dumonyu:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Why don't you spend your time more constructively and lobby to get your power increased, rather than take power away from others.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I for one do not think that 300 DPS for relatively ordinary cost and risk is appropriate.  I do not care to see melee damage dealers obsolete.  Likewise, it would be awful if the only balancing factor for mages is the existance of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Call of the Archmage</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  First, because it still obsoletes melees, and second, because it limits mages to a very few encounters, unlike enchanters whose charm is broadly applicable.<br>
<br>
In order to balance this exclusively through upgrades, based on what I have seen, the damage output of non-charming damage dealers would have to be approximately doubled.  As it is pretty clear that that would break the existing game, it seems hard to avoid the conclusion that charm is broken.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Goladus:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Used this log found in this thread....name ... damage ... dps<br>
Pets ... 781,578 ... 251<br>
Ranger ... 502,459 ... 162<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Is this evidence of a problem?<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Cantatus:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I have a few logs, nothing too conclusive though.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Thank you, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Cantatus</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  What we need here are more facts and fewer flames.<br>
<br>
So my first question is beginning to be answered.  Do charmed mobs do 300-500 DPS, and the answer appears to be yes, they can, depending on downtime, which effects melees similarly.<br>
<br>
The second question is whether this is balanced or not.  The logs suggest only normal risk, as downtime was not excessive and no player deaths were reported.<br>
<br>
The third question remains.  What is the cost of balancing this?  Will the fix be a global change that will impact ordinary pet owners more than charmers?  Can a fair solution be devised that retains most of the abilities and power of the effected classes, while preserving the role of non-charming damage dealers, especially melees?<br>
<br>
I for one refuse to be bought off with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Call of the Archmage</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  What I am seeing here seems suspiciously as if some players realize that they have an exploit here, and wish to milk it for loot and experience as long as possible before it is fixed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
